{"title_page": "Extra (service areas)", "text_new": "{{short description|British company operating service stations}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Extra MSA\n| logo = \n| type = [[Private company|Private]]\n| foundation = \n| location = [[Beaconsfield]], [[England]], [[United Kingdom|UK]]\n| key_people = \n| area_served = [[England]]\n| industry = [[Hospitality]]\n| revenue = \n| operating_income = \n| net_income = \n| num_employees = \n| parent = \n| subsid = \n| homepage = {{url|https://www.extraservices.co.uk/}}\n| footnotes = \n}}\n\n'''Extra MSA Services Ltd''' is a company which operates 9 [[Motorway#Motorway service areas|motorway service stations]] in [[England]], mainly on primary routes. It is based at Beaconsfield services, previously being in the centre of [[Lincoln, England|Lincoln]]. It is also known as Extra MSA Forecourts Ltd. \n\nMany of the brands at Extra locations including 'M&S Simply Food', 'Costa' and 'Greggs' are operated by [[Moto Hospitality|Moto]], the UK's largest service area operator and Extra's biggest competitor.\n\n==Market position==\nExtra is the fourth largest service station operator in the UK behind [[Moto Hospitality|Moto]] (1st), [[Welcome Break]] (2nd) and [[RoadChef]] (3rd). It came into operation after the government deregulated motorway services to encourage more competition and its first site opened in December 2000, at Cambridge. Peterborough opened in January 2001 and Baldock in July 2001.{{Citation needed|date=December 2011}}\n\n==Outlets==\n\n=== Service stations ===\nExtra developed its first three service stations at a cost of \u00a360m. The parent company was set up in 1992 by Stephen Spouge, who is now Chairman. Its service stations are designed by Nash and Partners of [[West Sussex]].<ref>[http://www.nashandpartners.co.uk/ss_petroleum.php#motorway_service_areas \"Motorway Service Areas\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090106003821/http://www.nashandpartners.co.uk/ss_petroleum.php#motorway_service_areas#motorway_service_areas |date=2009-01-06 }}, Nashandpartners.co.uk. Retrieved 3 December 2011</ref> The fuel reservoirs are built by WEFCO of [[Gainsborough, Lincolnshire|Gainsborough]]. It originally planned 17 service stations and currently operates a total of 9 service stations, and 2 petrol stations at competitor owned sites:\n* [[Baldock services|Baldock]] - [[A1 road (Great Britain)|A1]]/[[A1(M) motorway|A1(M)]] J10, via [[A507 road|A507]]\n* [[Beaconsfield services|Beaconsfield]] - [[M40 motorway|M40]] J2, via [[A355 road|A355]]\n* Blackburn with Darwen - [[M65 motorway|M65]] J4\n* Cambridge - [[A14 road (England)|A14]] J28\n* [[Cullompton services|Cullompton]] - [[M5 motorway|M5]] J28\n* Peterborough -  [[A1 road (Great Britain)|A1]]/[[A1(M) motorway|A1(M)]] J17, via [[A605 road|A605]]\n* [[Cobham services|Cobham]] - [[M25 motorway|M25]] between J9 & J10\n*Leeds Skelton Lake - M1 J45\n\n=== Petrol stations with basic services ===\n* [[Tibshelf services|Tibshelf]] (formerly Chesterfield) - [[M1 motorway (Great Britain)|M1]] between J28 & J29\n* [[Winchester services|Winchester]] - [[M3 motorway (Great Britain)|M3]] between J8 & J9\n\n=== Future stations ===\nExtra is currently the fastest developing service station operator in the UK with three areas opening, one each year up to 2010. The most recent station to open was at Leeds Skelton Lake in March 2020. Future sites plan to maximise areas of the road system that have few service areas, and will be developed by Swayfields Ltd, who own the Extra company.\n\nService stations due to open:\n* Sheffield - [[M1 motorway|M1]] J35 <ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sheffieldmotorwayservices.co.uk/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2014-03-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927123857/http://www.sheffieldmotorwayservices.co.uk/ |archive-date=2013-09-27 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* Solihull - [[M42 motorway|M42]] between J5 & J6\n\nProposed stations:\n* Chalfont St Peter - [[M25 motorway|M25]] between J16 and J17<ref>{{cite web |title=M25 West MSA |url=https://www.m25westmsa.co.uk/ |website=Extra MSA |accessdate=3 February 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Facilities==\n===Restaurants===\n* McDonald's\n* KFC\n* Chopstix\n* El Mexicana\n* JD Wetherspoon\n* Greggs (operated by [[Moto Hospitality|Moto]])\n* Nando's\n* Wrapchic\n* Carvery Express\n* Chozen Noodle\n*Chozen Sushi\n* Tossed\n\n===Coffee houses===\n* Starbucks Coffee\n* [[Costa Coffee]] (operated by Moto)\n\n===Retail outlets===\n* WHSmith\n* M&S Simply Food (operated by Moto)\n* [[Quicksilver (company)|Quicksilver gambling/amusement arcades]]\n*Top Gifts\n\n===Petrol stations===\n* Shell\n* BP\n\n===Hotels===\n* Days Inn\n*Ramada\n* Travelodge\n* [[ibis Budget]]\n\n==See also==\n* [[Rest area]]\n* [[Moto Hospitality|Moto]]\n* [[Welcome Break]]\n* [[RoadChef]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* [https://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/news/packer-jnr-in-163400m-move-to-add-to-his-menu-of-motorway-services-816042.html ''Independent'' April 2008]\n* [http://business.timesonline.co.uk/tol/business/specials/rich_list/article3798276.ece ''Times'' April 2008]\n* [http://forecourttrader.co.uk/news/fullstory.php/aid/1871/Shell_takes_control_of_Swayfields_sites.html ''Forecourt Trader'' September 2007]\n* [http://www.propertyweek.com/story.asp?storyCode=3073208 ''Property Week'' September 2006]\n* [http://www.businessweekly.co.uk/2000110223440/travel-and-transport-archive/150-jobs-in-a1m-project.html ''Business Weekly'' November 2000]{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.extraservices.co.uk Extra (Official Website)]\n* [http://motorwayservicesonline.co.uk/operators/extra/ Motorway Services Online - Extra]\n\n{{UK Motorway Service Stations}}\n\n[[Category:Catering and food service companies of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Buckinghamshire]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Lincoln, England]]\n[[C